article.headline: Bradley 107, Florida A&M 75
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- Danny Adams' 24 points, off 8-of-12 three-point shooting, led six Bradley players in double figures for a 107-75 win over Florida A&M on Tuesday night. Andrew Warren had 16 points off the bench for the Braves (4-0). Jeremy Crouch and Zach Andrews added 14 and 13 points, respectively, combining to go 7-for-7 from the foul line. Florida A&M (1-4) got 21 points from Rome Sanders, 13 from Jon Mason and 11 apiece from Darius Glover and Leslie Robinson. Both teams shot about 55 percent for the game, but Bradley took advantage of the Rattlers' mistakes, scoring 38 points off Florida A&M turnovers. The Braves took a 48-35 lead into halftime and built on it with 19-of-29 (65.5 percent) shooting after the break, when the Rattlers went 15-of-32 (46.9 percent) and Bradley led by as many as 39 points.
